<article>
    <h1>{{_ MTGO Traders League}}</h1>

    <p><a href="{{signup_url}}">{{_ Sign Up Here}}</a></p>

    <p>{{_ Each league lasts roughly a month. The [current league]({records_url}) will run until {end_date}.}}</p>

    <p><b>{{_ You can [sign up]({signup_url}) at any time.}}</b></p>

    <p>{{_ When you complete a five match league run for the first time ever you will get 1 tik credit with MTGO Traders (at the end of the month). This credit will appear when you trade with one of their bots on Magic Online.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ A league run is five matches against five different decks/opponents.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ Your deck stays the same through a run but you can change decks for each run (or not if you want to play again with the same deck).}}</p>

    <p>{{_ You can only have one run going at once.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ If you don't want to finish a league run message `!retire` to PDBot on Magic Online or [retire]({retire_url}) via the website and your run will end.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ Your deck will be checked for legality when you [sign up]({signup_url}).}}</p>

    <p>{{_ The easiest way to sign up is to export your deck from Magic Online and then upload it or copy it into the [sign up page]({signup_url}).}}</p>

    <p>{{_ To export your deck from Magic Online, right click on the name of the deck on the left of the Collection tab, then click export.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ PDBot will report your match result if it is watching your match but if not the winner should [report the result]({report_url}) of the match.}}</p>

    <p>{{_ Make sure you have the right deck name for both you and your opponent before submitting. Report any problems on [Discord]({discord_url}).}}</p>

    <p>{{_ Please do not report "non-games" such as your opponent timing out without ever deciding whether to mulligan or not.}}</p>

    <section>
        <h2>{{_ Prizes}}</h2>
            <p>{{_ At the end of each month, the top eight players of that month's league scoreboard will get credit with MTGO Traders (6/4/3/2/1/1/1/1). This credit will appear when you trade with one of their bots on Magic Online.}}</p>
            <p>{{_ For each match you won, you get one point. For each perfect (5-0) run you have, you get an extra point.}}</p>
            <p>{{_ You can enter the league as many times as you want.}}</p>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>{{_ Finding a Match}}</h2>
        <p>{{_ The easiest way to find a match to to simply play PD games with your league deck.  PDBot will alert you if both players are registered in league. Add "Penny Dreadful League" in a comment on your match in Just for Fun, Freeform to make your intentions clear.}}</p>
        <p>{{_ You can also find opponents through the #league channel on [Discord]({discord_url}).}}</li>
        <p>{{_ Matches should use 25 minute timers.}}</p>
    </section>

